jargo-client-react
==================

A browser client (classic WebRTC) and React bindings for jargo voice servers
(https://github.com/gojargo/jargo).

This is original work. It speaks the RTVI protocol (the real-time voice
interface used by Pipecat, created by Daily) so it can interoperate with
jargo's RTVI/WebRTC transport. "Pipecat" and "RTVI" are referenced here solely
for accurate description of the wire protocol; this project is independent and
not affiliated with, sponsored by, or endorsed by Daily.

